Average Inhibition at 8.5 uM: Normalized average percent inhibition of the counterscreen at a compound concentration of 8.5 micromolar.
Standard Deviation: Standard deviation derived from the normalized percent inhibition of the triplicate data for each compound.
Inhibition at 8.5 uM [1]: Normalized percent inhibition of the confirmation screen at a compound concentration of 8.5 uM. Replicate 1.
Inhibition at 8.5 uM [2]: Normalized percent inhibition of the confirmation screen at a compound concentration of 8.5 uM. Replicate 2.
Inhibition at 8.5 uM [3]: Normalized percent inhibition of the confirmation screen at a compound concentration of 8.5 uM. Replicate 3.
